  <original-body>Actionmailer deliberately removes the character set from attachments (line 71 of part.rb simply says: ctype_attrs.delete &quot;charset&quot;)

While this may make sense for pictures and binaries, there are several attachments types where a charset may be necessary, such as text files, html files and icalendar attachments.

One way to solve it would be to add something like: unless real_content_type.contains?('text')</original-body>
